Clodius was twice married, first to Pinaria and nsterward to Ful- via. He left a son, Publius, and a daughter. He inherited no property from his father. Resides what he obtained by less honest means, he received some moneys by legacies, and by letting one of his houses on the Palatino. He also received a considerable dowry with his wife Fulvia. He was the owner ’of two bouses on the Palatine Hill, an estate near Alba, and considerable possessione in Etruria, near Lake Prelius. His persona! appearance was effemi- nate, and neither handsome nor commanding.
